would there?

13:17.197 --> 13:20.165
What I mean is, when you,
if you select me.

13:20.167 --> 13:22.367
I'll be far away with an alibi.

13:22.369 --> 13:24.102
I don't mean to be rude,

13:24.104 --> 13:26.204
I just think it's
best to be up front.

13:26.206 --> 13:29.374
You don't expect me to
be here, to help you?

13:29.376 --> 13:32.377
- This is not the process.

13:32.379 --> 13:34.212
- What?

13:34.214 --> 13:35.346
- The process,
it's not the process.

13:35.348 --> 13:36.815
- What's the process?

13:36.817 --> 13:38.183
- First we talk about your work,

13:38.185 --> 13:40.385
and then I, I was probably...

13:40.387 --> 13:44.155
- well that stuff that I sent
you is actually quite old.

13:44.157 --> 13:45.957
I just sent it because it seems

13:45.959 --> 13:47.826
to do well with the
editors of magazines.

13:47.828 --> 13:49.027
I'd like to show you what
I'm writing currently.

13:49.029 --> 13:50.461
- Show me.

13:50.463 --> 13:54.199
- It's uh, it's an epic poem.

13:54.201 --> 13:56.467
Or well, considering that idea.

13:56.469 --> 13:59.170
It's uh, well,
better to show you.

14:15.487 --> 14:18.189
- Cimputer, hmm?

14:18.191 --> 14:20.191
Ever been to the Tate
modern in London?

14:20.193 --> 14:21.993
- No.

14:21.995 --> 14:22.994
- But you've been to
modern art museums.

14:22.996 --> 14:24.562
- Of course.

14:24.564 --> 14:26.564
It seems ironic now,
but I actually wrote my

14:26.566 --> 14:28.366
undergraduate thesis on the
transgressive corporeality

14:28.368 --> 14:30.101
of mannequins and humans
in the early work of -

14:30.103 --> 14:32.403
- imagine three people
in a modern art museum.

14:32.405 --> 14:34.505
The first is a pot-bellied
father of four from

14:34.507 --> 14:38.142
Kentucky or provincial France
or middle Russia somewhere.

14:38.144 --> 14:41.412
He's a tourist, he only
likes landscapes and nudes

14:41.414 --> 14:43.448
and paintings of
battles and ships.

14:43.450 --> 14:46.417
