like a tourist from Kentucky.

16:13.239 --> 16:15.406
You're not part
of the cool crowd.

16:15.408 --> 16:17.442
Other people get it,
not you though.

16:17.444 --> 16:20.278
And then I hear a
third voice in my head.

16:20.280 --> 16:22.113
No, Maya, it's
okay, you do get it,

16:22.115 --> 16:24.148
this really is a
mediocre painting.

16:24.150 --> 16:25.683
This really could've
been painted

16:25.685 --> 16:28.453
by a kid or even a cimputer.

16:30.255 --> 16:34.325
And then the people in
my head start arguing.

16:36.428 --> 16:38.329
- Are you saying
that my work is...

16:38.331 --> 16:40.331
- shit?

16:40.333 --> 16:44.469
Not quite, it's more like
chewed but undigested food.

16:46.171 --> 16:49.140
You're young,
there's hope for you.

16:57.249 --> 16:59.584
- In the back corner.

16:59.586 --> 17:00.651
That piece.

17:03.255 --> 17:06.023
Do you consider that good art?

17:06.026 --> 17:08.459
- That's a different
story, that's not paint.

17:08.461 --> 17:11.796
That's blood and
human brain matter.

17:11.798 --> 17:14.732
Isn't that terrible?

17:14.733 --> 17:18.336
But hey, you like cerebral art.

17:20.204 --> 17:22.073
She had lung cancer.

17:22.075 --> 17:24.308
That was her very last
painting, a perverse friend

17:24.310 --> 17:28.246
